title: Netflix throws Meghan’s show in the ‘do not resuscitate pile’ after distancing themselves from her
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ podcast host Kinsey Schofield is grateful Netflix threw Meghan Markle’s cooking show in the “do not resuscitate pile”.   “Netflix has worked so hard to distance themselves from the show instead of promoting it,” Ms Schofield told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “There were reports that Meghan was having secret meetings to try to save the show, but Netflix doesn’t believe that the return on investment is there.”

title: David and Victoria Beckham will only speak to Brooklyn if he ‘splits’ from Nicola Peltz
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi calls this week for the Beckham family “chaotic”.   “We saw earlier this week that extraordinary statement from eldest son, Brooklyn, lashing out at his parents, particularly his mother, Victoria,” Ms Panahi said.  “David and Victoria Beckham would be gutted naturally, but sources are saying they are blaming Nicolae, their son’s wife, not him.  “They’re only going to speak to him if he splits from her.”

title: ‘Government isn’t listening’: Report reveals CFA funding drop
description: Sky News host Peta Credlin sits down with Watchem CFA Captain Chris Colbert to discuss the Labor government cutting CFA's funding by $55 million in real terms since 2020.

title: ‘She’s a terrible influence’: David and Victoria Beckham label Nicola Peltz a ‘troublemaker’
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ podcast host Kinsey Schofield claims David and Victoria Beckham find their daughter-in-law, Nicola Peltz, a “pretty terrible influence” on Brooklyn Beckham.    “They have tried to communicate with him without her presence for years at this point,” Ms Schofield told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “They just want one-on-one time with their son.  “They are desperate for privacy and to set the record straight without Nicola, who seems to be a troublemaker and an instigator.”

title: Jewish community ‘forever changed’ after Bondi Beach massacre
description: Opposition Leader Sussan Ley addresses the ‘Light Will Win’ memorial, saying the Jewish community was “forever changed that night”.   “15 lights that must never go out, each life was precious, each was deeply loved, and each leaves behind family, friends, and a community forever changed by that night,” Ms Ley said.  “To those who grieve, to the survivors… we hold you close today.”

title: ‘Most painful days of my life’: Rabbi reflects on the aftermath of the Bondi terror attack
description: Chabad of Bondi Spiritual Leader Rabbi Yehoram Ulman says despite the “pain” of the Bondi terror attack, the days following the tragedy sparked an “awakening” across Australia.  “The past 30 days or more have been the most painful days of my life,” Mr Ulman said.  “I believe I speak for many when I say we’ve felt an emptiness so heavy it could crush us.  “But in that void, something else appeared … these 30 days I have witnessed an awakening in a country I’ve never seen before.”

title: ‘Extraordinary humanity’: Sussan Ley commends ‘courage’ of first responders in Bondi attack
description: Opposition Leader Sussan Ley addresses the ‘Light Will Win’ memorial, saying that in the midst of the “darkness”, extraordinary humanity was witnessed among people.   “In the midst of that darkness, we also witnessed extraordinary humanity, strangers protected strangers, ordinary Australians acted with courage and selflessness,” Ms Ley said.  “Those acts don’t lessen the pain, but they remind us of who we are.”

title: Donald Trump signs Gaza peace charter with world leaders
description: US President Donald Trump has signed the Gaza peace charter in Davos with other world leaders.

title: ‘Staggering’ the Coalition ‘blow itself up’ over Labor’s hate speech laws
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand claims it is “staggering” the Coalition split over Labor’s hate speech laws.  “Having a weak opposition or an opposition that, at the moment, we don’t even know if it exists … the fact it’s managed to blow itself up over this issue is absolutely staggering,” Mr Hildebrand told Sky News host Paul Murray.   “They went too hard, and they went too personal in trying to blame Albo for the Bondi terror attack.”

title: Children are being ‘indoctrinated’ in schools to be shameful for Australia’s history
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says children are being “indoctrinated” in schools to be shameful for Australia’s history.

title: ‘We need to pull our socks up’: Coalition splits over hate speech reforms
description: Nationals senator Ross Cadell says the Liberal Party and National Party need to pull their “socks up” amid a split between the Coalition.   “This wasn’t planned, this wasn’t hoped for, it’s catch-up football on both sides,” Mr Cadell told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “We just need to just pull our socks up.”

title: Teachers in the UK report young children don’t have ‘basic language skills’
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says teachers in the UK have reported that young children do not have “basic language skills”.

title: NSW mother has ‘spoken out’ after her child brings home shocking colouring book project
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says a NSW mother has “spoken out” after her child brought home colouring books about being sorry to Indigenous Australians.

title: UK teachers sound the alarm for children’s readiness coming into first year of school
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says a survey in the UK shows teachers sounding the alarm for the readiness of children coming into their first year of school.

title: Bondi Beach massacre was fuelled by ‘darkness and hate’
description: Opposition Leader Sussan Ley addresses the ‘Light Will Win’ memorial, reminiscing on the Bondi Beach massacre and the “darkness and hate” which occurred.   “This attack took place on the first night of Hanukkah, the festival of lights, a night that should have been filled with joy and hope was instead marked by darkness and hate,” Ms Ley said.  “Many never imagined such a thing could happen here in Australia … the luckiest of lucky countries.”
